prompt:
Count the strings of length 14 over the alphabet {P, Q, R} that satisfy ALL four conditions simultaneously:
(a) no two adjacent letters are equal;
(b) the letter P appears exactly five times;
(c) the letter Q is never immediately followed by the letter R (the substring "QR" never occurs anywhere in the string);
(d) the first letter of the string and the last letter of the string are different.
Give the exact count. Put the final integer inside \boxed{}.
